public PSSimpleKey(String keyName,
                   String value,
                   boolean persisted)
Create an assigned key with a single part. The persisted property is dtermined by parameter persisted.

Parameters:
keyName - The name for the key, typically, the column name of the primary key of the associated table.
value - The value for the key. It may not be null or empty.
persisted - A flag to indicate whether this key represents a a component that exists in the db. Realize that this is a snapshot, so the component represented by this key could be removed while this key is instantiated.
